CVE stands for Common Vulnerabilities and Exposures. -- in our pom.xml

A CVE is a unique ID given to a known security vulnerability.

👉 Think of it like:

“Tracking number for a security bug”

Example

CVE-2021-44228

This refers to the famous Log4j vulnerability (Log4Shell).

Breakdown of CVE ID

CVE-2021-44228
│    │     │
│    │     └── Unique number
│    └──────── Year discovered
└───────────── CVE identifier

Why CVEs are important
Standard way to identify vulnerabilities

Used by tools like:
Snyk
Trivy
Sysdig

Helps teams:
Track issues
Prioritize fixes
Search solutions easily

