Real CVE Examples with Solutions:

------------------------------------------------------------
1) CVE-2021-44228 (Log4Shell)
------------------------------------------------------------
Issue:
- Remote Code Execution in Apache Log4j

Impact:
- Attacker can run code on server

Solution:
- Upgrade Log4j to 2.17+
- Disable JNDI lookups (temporary fix)
- Restrict outbound network access if needed

------------------------------------------------------------
2) CVE-2022-22965 (Spring4Shell)
------------------------------------------------------------
Issue:
- Remote Code Execution in Spring Framework

Impact:
- Full application compromise

Solution:
- Upgrade Spring Framework
- Restrict data binding
- Use WAF rules (temporary)

------------------------------------------------------------
3) CVE-2014-0160 (Heartbleed)
------------------------------------------------------------
Issue:
- OpenSSL memory leak

Impact:
- Exposes passwords, keys, sensitive data

Solution:
- Patch OpenSSL
- Rotate SSL certificates
- Reset user passwords

------------------------------------------------------------
4) CVE-2014-6271 (Shellshock)
------------------------------------------------------------
Issue:
- Bash executes malicious environment variables

Impact:
- Remote command execution

Solution:
- Patch Bash
- Restrict CGI scripts
- Sanitize inputs

------------------------------------------------------------
5) CVE-2016-5195 (Dirty COW)
------------------------------------------------------------
Issue:
- Linux privilege escalation

Impact:
- Normal user becomes root

Solution:
- Update Linux kernel
- Limit unnecessary user access

------------------------------------------------------------
6) CVE-2017-0144 (EternalBlue)
------------------------------------------------------------
Issue:
- SMB vulnerability (used in WannaCry)

Impact:
- Remote exploitation, ransomware spread

Solution:
- Apply Microsoft patch
- Disable SMBv1
- Block port 445 if not needed

------------------------------------------------------------
7) CVE-2018-1002105 (Kubernetes API)
------------------------------------------------------------
Issue:
- Privilege escalation in Kubernetes

Impact:
- Unauthorized cluster access

Solution:
- Upgrade Kubernetes
- Apply RBAC rules
- Restrict API access

------------------------------------------------------------
8) CVE-2019-5736 (Docker runC)
------------------------------------------------------------
Issue:
- Container escape vulnerability

Impact:
- Access host from container

Solution:
- Update Docker / runC
- Avoid running containers as root
- Use AppArmor / SELinux

------------------------------------------------------------
Common Fix Pattern:
------------------------------------------------------------
1. Upgrade vulnerable version
2. Apply security patch
3. Change configuration
4. Restrict access (network/IAM)

