"I use Declarative Pipelines in Jenkins. Let me walk you through a real pipeline I set up for a Java Spring Boot application that deploys to AWS EKS."

Stage 1 - Checkout:
  "Pull latest code from GitHub
   main branch automatically"

Stage 2 - Build:
  "Maven compiles Java code
   creates JAR file
   archives as Jenkins artifact"

Stage 3 - Test:
  "Runs JUnit tests
   publishes test reports
   pipeline fails if tests fail"

Stage 4 - Docker Build:
  "Creates Docker image
   tags with build number
   also tags as latest"

Stage 5 - Push to ECR:
  "Authenticates with AWS
   creates ECR repo if not exists
   pushes both tags to ECR"

Stage 6 - Update Kubeconfig:
  "Connects Jenkins to EKS
   verifies nodes are running"

Stage 7 - Deploy to EKS:
  "Replaces IMAGE_PLACEHOLDER
   applies Deployment.yaml
   waits for rollout
   verifies pods running"

Post actions:
  "Cleans Docker images
   cleans workspace
   always runs regardless
   of success or failure"
