SonarQube — Why After Build (mvn)

SonarQube scans:
  ✅ compiled Java code
  ✅ test coverage reports
  ✅ code quality issues
  ✅ bugs and vulnerabilities

Needs:
  ✅ compiled .class files
  ✅ test results
  ✅ JAR already built

Cannot scan:
  ❌ before build
  ❌ needs compiled code
  ❌ not just source code

Snyk — Why Scan pom.xml

Snyk scans:
  ✅ pom.xml dependencies
  ✅ finds vulnerable libraries
  ✅ example:
     log4j vulnerability ❌
     spring security bug ❌

Scans BEFORE Docker build:
  ✅ catch issues early
  ✅ no point building Docker
     if dependencies vulnerable ❌
  ✅ fail fast ✅
